HOW DO YOU KNOW THIS GUY ANYWAY?
那你是怎么认识这个人的？

228
00:10:13,847 --> 00:10:15,981
HE'S THAT INVESTMENT BANKER IN MY PARENTS' BUILDING
他是个投资银行家，跟我住一栋楼

229
00:10:15,983 --> 00:10:17,716
I USED TO HOOK UP WITH IN HIGH SCHOOL.
高中时我们在一起过

230
00:10:17,718 --> 00:10:19,384
OH, MY GOD.HE'S THAT GUY.
惹，原来就是这个家伙啊

231
00:10:19,386 --> 00:10:22,754
YEAH, SO HE LOST HIS JOB, BECAME A STAY-AT-HOME DAD,
是的，他丢了工作，现在就做一个全职父亲

232
00:10:22,756 --> 00:10:24,122
AND GOT INTO LIGHT DRUGS.
并且磕点药

233
00:10:24,124 --> 00:10:25,223
GOOD FOR HIM.
挺适合他的

234
00:10:25,225 --> 00:10:26,791
SO, DO YOU HAVE A LESSON PLAN?
所以你有教学计划吗？

235
00:10:26,793 --> 00:10:28,193
WHAT IS THIS, GERMANY?
教学计划？我才没那么严谨

236
00:10:28,195 --> 00:10:29,394
THEY'RE PARK SLOPE TEENS.
这就是群布鲁克林学生而已

237
00:10:29,396 --> 00:10:30,895
I COULD LOCK 'EM IN A ROOM
我可以把他们锁在一个房间里

238
00:10:30,897 --> 00:10:32,130
WITH A HALF-EATEN APPLE AND A TIC TAC
再放个啃了一半的苹果让他们随便拍

239
00:10:32,132 --> 00:10:33,331
AND COME BACK TO THE "MONA LISA."
等家长来接的时候再装装样子就好了

240
00:10:33,333 --> 00:10:34,833
WH-- WHY ARE WE STOPPING?
我们怎么停下了

241
00:10:34,835 --> 00:10:36,067
OH, I HAVE TO TAKE CARE OF SOMETHING.
我有些事情需要处理

242
00:10:36,069 --> 00:10:37,402
YOU WAIT OUT HERE.
你在外面等着
NO, NO, NO, WAIT.
不不，等一下

243
00:10:37,404 --> 00:10:38,937
OH, PLEASE DON'T DO THIS.
别这么做

244
00:10:38,939 --> 00:10:41,139
YOU SAID THAT NO AMOUNT OF WHOLESALE SPELT SUSHI
你说过，你凡是在这儿批发的寿司

245
00:10:41,141 --> 00:10:43,775
WAS WORTH THE EMOTIONAL TOLL OF BEING HERE.
可全都是意气用事，完全不值啊！

246
00:10:43,777 --> 00:10:45,343
SHE'S HERE ALL THE TIME.
但是Maxine一直在这里啊

247
00:10:45,345 --> 00:10:49,014
THEY DON'T EVEN OFFER PAPER BAGS.
他们甚至连个纸袋都不给你

248
00:10:49,016 --> 00:10:52,417
IT'S SURPRISING HOW, UH, LONELY IT GETS
一个人竟然能感觉这么孤独

249
00:10:52,419 --> 00:10:54,419
WHEN YOU'RE SINGLE AGAIN,
当他回归单身

250
00:10:54,421 --> 00:10:55,954
ESPECIALLY WHEN YOU LIVE WITH SOMEONE.
尤其是，他曾和别人一起生活过

251
00:10:55,956 --> 00:10:57,689
YOU GET SO USED TO THEIR HABITS
早已习惯另一半的爱好

252
00:10:57,691 --> 00:10:59,224
AND THEIR LIFESTYLE AND THEIR SMELLS,
他们的生活习惯，他们的气味

253
00:10:59,226 --> 00:11:01,760
BUT, UM, I REALLY JOINED THE CO-OP
我真的加入了她在的那个消费合作社

254
00:11:01,762 --> 00:11:03,328
TO SPEND TIME WITH HER,'CAUSE, LET'S BE HONEST,
就为了能跟她在一起，但说实话

255
00:11:03,330 --> 00:11:06,064
IT'S NOT THE MOST PLEASANT PLACE TO WORK IN THE WORLD.
那儿并不舒服

256
00:11:06,066 --> 00:11:08,299
BUT IF I REALLY WANT MAXINE BACK IN MY LIFE,
但如果我真的希望Maxine回到我身边

257
00:11:08,301 --> 00:11:10,235
I'M GONNA HAVE TO DO WHATEVER IT TAKES,
我会愿意付出任何代价

258
00:11:10,237 --> 00:11:12,370
AND THAT MEANS GETTING BACK ONTO HER CO-OP SHIFT,
那就意味着我要去参加她在的合作社

259
00:11:12,372 --> 00:11:14,839
AND THAT'S WHERE YOU COME IN.
当然，也就是你这里

260
00:11:14,841 --> 00:11:16,675
IT-- IT SAYS IN YOUR FILE
根据你的档案

261
00:11:16,677 --> 00:11:19,010
THAT YOU HAVEN'T WORKED A SHIFT IN FOUR MONTHS.
你已经四个月没参与工作了

262
00:11:19,012 --> 00:11:20,445
EXTENUATING CIRCUMSTANCES.
特殊情况，情有可原啊

263
00:11:20,447 --> 00:11:22,447
I'VE HAD A VERY BROKEN HEART.
那段时间我真的很心碎

264
00:11:23,916 --> 00:11:26,117
LOOK, ALL MEMBERS ARE ENTITLED
诚然，所有的成员在失职之后

265
00:11:26,119 --> 00:11:28,153
TO ONE FREE PASS AFTER A DELINQUENCY,
都有一次被原谅的机会

266
00:11:28,155 --> 00:11:30,155
BUT I CANNOT GET YOU ONTO HER SHIFT.
但我还是不能把你调去她那边

267
00:11:30,157 --> 00:11:31,322
IT'S ALL BOOKED.
满员了

268
00:11:34,326 --> 00:11:36,194
I'M SORRY, I DIDN'T CATCH YOUR NAME.
对不起，你的名字是？

269
00:11:36,196 --> 00:11:37,328
JACKIE.

270
00:11:37,330 --> 00:11:38,930
HI, JACKIE.

271
00:11:38,932 --> 00:11:40,799
UM...

272
00:11:40,801 --> 00:11:45,070
THE LAST TIME I CHECKED, THIS IS A COOPERATIVE.
我知道这是个合作社

273
00:11:45,072 --> 00:11:47,405
WHY DON'T YOU GO AHEAD AND COOPERATE WITH ME,
既然这样，你就帮我个忙，和我合作一下

274
00:11:47,407 --> 00:11:49,874
AND I'LL COOPERATE WITH YOU.
我也会好好工作，这样不好吗？

275
00:11:52,344 --> 00:11:55,280
BUT HOW DO YOU GET THEM SO CURLY?
你是怎么把它们弄得那么卷的？

276
00:11:55,282 --> 00:11:56,414
LET'S GO.
我们走吧

277
00:11:56,416 --> 00:11:58,750
IT WAS SO NICE MEETING YOU.
很高兴认识你

278
00:12:14,967 --> 00:12:16,735
SHIRIN TOLD ME YOU'RE AN ARTIST.
Shirin告诉我你是一个艺术家

279
00:12:16,737 --> 00:12:18,436
LANDSCAPING OR PORTRAITS?
是擅长景物还是人像呢？

280
00:12:18,438 --> 00:12:21,039
I SPECIALIZE IN EXPERIMENTAL INSTALLATIONS,
我擅长搞实验性的装置艺术

281
00:12:21,041 --> 00:12:23,408
AND JACQUES IS CURRENTLY FOCUSING ON SANDCASTLE WORK
Jacques最近在忙他的沙雕

282
00:12:23,410 --> 00:12:25,977
INTEGRATING FOUND OBJECTS.
把他找的小东西组合成艺术品

283
00:12:25,979 --> 00:12:27,512
WE'RE DONE WITH THE BOXES.
我们搬完箱子了

284
00:12:27,514 --> 00:12:28,913
I'M COMING.
我就来

285
00:12:28,915 --> 00:12:30,482
IT WAS SO NICE MEETING YOU.
很高兴认识你

286
00:12:31,984 --> 00:12:33,985
THERE'S NO TOILET PAPER.
洗手间里没有厕纸了

287
00:12:38,057 --> 00:12:39,758
HEY, YOU GUYS CAN GO.
你们可以走了

288
00:12:39,760 --> 00:12:40,992
I FEEL LIKE I'M 17
我感觉我只有17岁

289
